### HYMN XLVI

#### A charm for offspring and prosperity

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0704601">1</span></span>O
broad-tressed Sinivāli, thou who art the sister of the Gods,  
  Accept the offered sacrifice, and, Goddess, grant us progeny.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0704602">2</span></span>Present the
sacrifice to her, to Sinivāli, Queen of men, Beauti-  
   ful-fingered, lovely-armed, prolific, bearing many a child.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0704603">3</span></span>Thou who as
Queen of men art Indra's equal, a Goddess  
   coming with a thousand tresses,  
  To thee our sacrifices are performed, O Consort of Vishnu  
  Goddess, urge thy Lord to bounty!

